## 2. Genre definition

[cite_start]One of the main challenges of studying genre is that there is no consensus among researchers on the definition of the genre phenomenon, or how to differentiate between genres[cite: 917].

**Terminology:**
[cite_start]While many researchers use the term "genre" and describe this task as "automatic genre identification" (AGI) or "web genre identification" (WGI), others avoid this term and prefer derived analogues, such as "registers", "functional text dimensions" or "text types"[cite: 922]. [cite_start]According to Lee (2002A), the largest difference between the concepts of genres and registers is that genres describe whole texts, while registers are defined based on internal linguistic patterns, which are independent of text-level structures[cite: 926].

**Defining Characteristics:**
[cite_start]In general, most definitions describe genre classes based on the socially recognized form of a document and its intended communicative purpose[cite: 928]. [cite_start]Some definitions also consider the target audience, expectations of the reader, style, or the content of the texts[cite: 929]. [cite_start]To identify genres, researchers observe their intrinsic features (text-internal perspective) or their extrinsic features (text-external or functional perspective)[cite: 930].

**Challenges of Digital Texts:**
Studying genres of digital texts is difficult due to several factors:
1.  **Evolution:** Conventional characteristics of a genre category can change over time. [cite_start]The evolution of genres was especially notable after the introduction of the World Wide Web, when researchers observed emergence of new genres and existing genres that evolved[cite: 932, 933].
2.  [cite_start]**Hybridity:** Some web documents can be hybrids, meaning a single text can display characteristics of multiple genres (e.g., an advertorial)[cite: 935].
3.  [cite_start]**Lack of Characteristics:** Some web documents might not have any discernible characteristics of a genre class or can be too short to reveal the purpose[cite: 936, 937].
4.  [cite_start]**Processing Issues:** Genre can only be realized in a complete text, which is not always available after extraction and boilerplate removal[cite: 939, 943].

