**Recent Comparability Studies:**
Kuzman and Pollak (2022a) explored comparability between Slovene GINCO and English CORE by mapping them to a joint schema. [cite_start]Experiments showed the datasets are comparable enough to allow cross-dataset/lingual transfer [cite: 1556-1559]. [cite_start]Interestingly, despite CORE being much larger, the difference in size did not result in significantly better results, suggesting Transformer models might only need a few thousand instances to learn genres effectively [cite: 1563-1564].

**Large-scale Application:**
Recent breakthroughs allowed applying classifiers to massive corpora.
* [cite_start]**Register Oscar:** A dataset of 351 million documents in 14 languages automatically annotated using a classifier trained on CORE [cite: 1585-1587].
* [cite_start]**MaCoCu:** Corpora for 10 under-resourced European languages automatically annotated with GINCO-based classifiers [cite: 1593-1594].

